{
  "doc_id": "33360",
  "text": "All images were evaluated before the statistical analysis for fracture displacement, implant positioning, and quality of reduction. Fracture displacement was assessed using the simplified undisplaced vs. displaced version of the Garden criteria [CITATION_1] , due to low reliability of the 4-grade system [CITATION_2] ). The implant positioning was assessed according to a modified version by [CITATION_3] (Figure 2 ). 1 point was given if: (1) the positions of the screws were within the central or caudal segment of the femoral head on the anterior-posterior view; (2) the distance between the tip of the screws and the articular margin of the femoral head was less than 10 mm; (3) the positioning of the lowest screw was directly over the calcar in anterior-posterior view: (4) the angle of the screws and the femur was more than 130 degrees; (5) the positions of the screws were within the central or dorsal part on the axial view.",
